article.description: DeAnthony McCallum had a career-high 22 points as Jacksonville defeated Kennesaw State 83-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: McCallum lifts Jacksonville past Kennesaw State 83-64
article.linkText: McCallum lifts Jacksonville past Kennesaw State 83-64
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- DeAnthony McCallum had a career-high 22 points as Jacksonville defeated Kennesaw State 83-64 on Saturday. Destin Barnes had 15 points for Jacksonville (10-12, 3-4 Atlantic Sun Conference). David Bell added 11 points. Bryce Workman had eight rebounds. Tyler Hooker scored a season-high 30 points for the Owls (1-19, 0-7), who have now lost 11 consecutive games. Ugo Obineke added 11 points. Jamie Lewis had 10 points. Jacksonville matches up against Florida Gulf Coast at home on Thursday.
